{
  "texts": [
    "The natural distribution follows Zips's law in that p s ∝ 1 r+Z, where r is the rank of s in descending order of frequency amongst s ∈ S, and Z is a constant.",
    "The following theorem uses the asymptotic complexity notations O and Ω for the upper and lower bound respectively.",
    "For any agnostic learning algorithm for F, ϵ is Ω(|S|/D) and O[(|S|/D) 0.5 ] Proof.",
    "We first prove the upper bound.",
    "Let ps and L(f, T) be the observed probabilities and loss respectively in a randomly chosen training subset of the corpus T."
  ]
}